Middleware middlewares intercept actions, modify them, or cancel them by not calling any of the next middleware.
Basically, middleware happens between dispatching an action, and the moment it reaches the reducer.
// Create a middleware // Logger const logger = store =&gt; next =&gt; action =&gt; { console.log('action fired', action) next(action) } // Apply middleware const middleware = applyMiddleware(logger) // create the store, pass it the middleware along with reducers and state const store = createStore(reducer, 1, middleware)  You&rsquo;re probably never gonna create middleware, you&rsquo;ll just npm install them.

