Importing files is handy when you have your css in multiple files instead of one bloated stylesheet. See Bootstrap&rsquo;s Sass files for an example. Every css component gets it&rsquo;s own .scss file and they all get compiled into one main stylesheet.
The usual imports in a main.scss file are something like this:
// Reset @import &quot;_reset.scss&quot;; // Definings @import &quot;_varables.scss&quot;; @import &quot;_mixins.scss&quot;; // Global Styles @imprt &quot;_globals.scss&quot;; // Page specifics @import &quot;pages/_about_us.

